+Feature: HCP Audience Workspace in Studio Application
+  
+  Background:
+    Given the user is on the portal login page
+    And the user logs in with valid credentials
+    And the user clicks on the Studio menu
+    And the user is navigated to the Studio application
+
+  Scenario: Create and save an HCP audience workspace with specific filters
+    When the user clicks on "Create New Workspace"
+    And the user sees the types of workspaces they have permissions for
+    Then the user clicks on "HCP Audiences" workspace
+    And the user selects the advertiser "<advertiser>"
+    And the user applies the following filters:
+      | Filter     | Value   |
+      | NPI Gender | <gender>|
+      | NPI Age    | <age>   |
+    And the user clicks "OK"
+    Then the filters should be applied to the workspace
+    And the user renames the workspace to "<workspace_name>"
+    And the user saves the workspace
+
+    Examples:
+      | advertiser | gender | age           | workspace_name       |
+      | Advertiser1| Male   | 25-35, 45-65  | Stud_automation_HCP  |
